Description: USED 2006 Fender Mexico 60th Anniversary Stratocaster Condition is a solid 8/10, it shows minimal signs of use, minimal fret wear, there is a finish crack near the bridge (see close up photo) Mexican Fenders are finished with Nitrocellulose which checks and cracks with age or extreme temperature changes. Includes a Fender gig bag, no tremolo arm, Original bridge pickup will be included, and DiMarzio packaging for the bridge pickup. DiMarzio Billy Corgan bucker installed in the bridge for a bit of extra oomph! The internal cavities of the guitar have been shielded with copper foil. Plays and sounds great, has a basic setup with 10-46 Gauge DR Pure Blues- I'll toss in a fresh pack of 10-46 Blues, HiBeam or TiteFit (all I keep on hand) with the sale. Just like any guitar you’ll need to have it set it up to your liking. Great candy Apple Red Color. This will be properly packed to insure a safe journey, I loosen the strings on the guitar for shipment, pad everything with bubble wrap and foam blocks. This has a 9.5" Radius board. • Guitar is used, sold as used, sold as-is, all sales final, no returns • Please be sure to check all the pictures and ask questions before bidding. Shipping to the lower 48 States is set at $30.00 FedEX Ground. No international.
